PT- J|
TI- THE EFFECT OF DIGITALISM ON SUPPLY CHAIN FLEXIBILITY OF FOOD INDUSTRY IN JORDAN|
AB- THIS STUDY COMES TO ASCERTAIN THE IMPACT OF DIGITALISM ON SUPPLY CHAIN FLEXIBILITY. A SAMPLE CONSISTING OF 350 EMPLOYEES WAS SELECTED FROM MANUFACTURING COMPANIES IN THE FOOD INDUSTRY TO COLLECT RESEARCH DATA. ONE INCLUSION CRITERION WAS ASSUMED IN THIS RESEARCH, WHICH IS EMPLOYEE KNOWLEDGE OF SUPPLY CHAIN PROCESSES. RESEARCH DATA WAS GATHERED USING A QUESTIONNAIRE DISTRIBUTED TO THE MEMBERS OF THE SAMPLE. THE FINAL NUMBER OF THE QUESTIONNAIRES WAS 297 WITH A RESPONSE RATE OF 85%. ANALYZING DATA VIA SMARTPLS 3.0, THE RESULTS INDICATED THAT INTERNET OF THINGS (IOT) HAD A SIGNIFICANT EFFECT ON SUPPLY CHAIN FLEXIBILITY. SUCH RESULTS CONFIRMED THAT ONE DIMENSION OF DIGITALISM, WHICH IS THE INTERNET OF THINGS, HAS A SIGNIFICANT EFFECT ON SUPPLY CHAIN FLEXIBILITY.|
