PT- J|
TI- SOCIO-ECOLOGICAL FACTORS AND WELL-BEING AMONG SELF-EMPLOYED IN EUROPE DURING THE COVID-19 PANDEMIC|
AB- THE FINDINGS HIGHLIGHT THAT THE SOCIO-ECOLOGICAL FACTORS OF RESILIENCE, SOCIAL SUPPORT, DOING USEFUL WORK AND FINDING THE RULES CLEAR AFFECT WELL-BEING. THE RESULTS ALSO INDICATE THAT IT IS VITAL TO CONSIDER FACTORS AT MULTIPLE SOCIO-ECOLOGICAL LEVELS TO IMPROVE THE WELL-BEING OF THE SELF-EMPLOYED DURING ADVERSITY.|
